        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 11 at 5:28PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 528 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southeast of Glencoe, or 15 miles east of Ruidoso, moving
south at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
San Patricio and Glencoe.

This includes Highway 380 near Mile Marker 105.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
